# Ignore everything, then whitelist only what the image needs. This keeps the
# build context small and, crucially, keeps local state (userdata/, .env, the
# SQLite DB) out of the image — at runtime that data is mounted from GCS.
**

# --- application ---
!src/
!pyproject.toml
!uv.lock
!README.md

# --- re-exclude junk that the src/ whitelist would otherwise pull back in ---
**/__pycache__/
**/*.pyc
.git/
